n_th element is used to find the value at some index 'i' if the array was sorted.
The first 'i' elements need not be  sorted.
It  can be also used to find the median.
Asymptotics : O(n)

Example:

vector<int>vec={3,1,7,2,8,4};
    nth_element(vec.begin(),vec.begin()+3,vec.end());
    for(auto x:vec)
        cout<<x<<' ';
 
 Output: 2 1 3 4 8 7 
 At the fourth position '4' must be present in the sorted array . 
